13/05/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Extremists attacked immigrants in Athens on Thursday (May 12th) during a demonstration by about 2,000 youths protesting Tuesday's killing of a Greek man.
Nationalists have blamed the crime on immigrants, although officials have found no evidence to substantiate that.
Police used tear gas to disperse protestors at Thursday's rally.
According to reports, at least 15 immigrants and one Greek were injured, while over 50 people were arrested.
(To Vima - 13/05/11;
ERT, Ta Nea - 12/05/11)
